		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I always end up copying my character's INI files and renaming them to get the same layout, Nolrog.<br><br>It's clumsy, and a PITA, but it works.<br><br>If I made a new character, then I would copy the existing files in my main EQ directory:<br><br>Meriad_mithanie.ini<br>UI_Meriad_mithanie.ini<br><br>to <br><br>Newcharacter_mithanie.ini<br>UI_Newcharacter_mithanie.ini<br><br>New character gets all the socials that way too, so if you have custom socials set up, you'll want to change them. You can even copy cross server by changing the server-name part to the correct server name. I beleive it's the first 8 characters of the server name. So If I were going to make a character on Ayonnae Ro, it'd be<br><br>Newcharacter_ayonnaer.ini<br>UI_Newcharacter_ayonnaer.ini<br><br>I would love to see a /copyini charactername to accomplish the same effect in the game, but it's not a priority for me since this works. <br><br>Theoretically, this would be better suited to go in the Patcher than the game binary so as not to add to the already bloated memory footprint.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<hr><font size=-3 color="#666666">The less-organized group of 'casual' monkies are left wondering what's wrong. The levers are now so difficult to push, they're left eating the crumbs of old cookies and whatever comes flying across the room. The only time a Jolly Rancher comes their way, it's already covered in spit and monkey-hair. They're hungry. And their teeth hurt. They need their vitamins and some sweet monkey lovin', but the stench from the 'hard-core' side of the lab makes it difficult to get romantic.<br><br>Good God, won't somone give the casual monkies some dental floss?!</font>
