<HR>
Garnash wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Delores wrote:<BR>
<DIV>The one feature I wish EQ had right now is this: characters on cancelled accounts should be automatically detagged from guilds. I know this would save my guild a lot of grief in tracking down who is gone for good versus on break/hiatus. It&nbsp;would also prevent&nbsp;many of the&nbsp;customer service issues with E-Bay'ed characters attempting to pose as the original owner to scam others.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>This would cause us who run on gamecards all kinds of trouble. Every time the game card ran out and we didn't have one on hand, our toons would be kicked from the guild. Not just those on game cards either, but those who cancel each month so their card gets charged at a bad moment.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>i play on game cards. you cant put in the code for the new card until the account runs out. (sometimes in the middle of playing)</P>
<P>while i always have a new card ready, deguilding me for that wouldnt be too good, lol im guild leader <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>
<P>perhaps, since you can see when the player was last logged in, on the guild tool, make a set time for deguilding players who havent been ingame for x weeks or months.</P>	
