<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
VorAbaddon wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Knew I'd remember what I really wanted to mention.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A command for the far clip, in addition to the slider. I chance far clip often, especially in OoW, where zoning with more than 50% far clip means a huge chance of LD/crash. I have four I'm normall set at: 0 ((Traveling and Zoning)), 25 ((Most OoW)), 50 ((Some OoW, and OoW when pulling)) and 100, ((Most other places))</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>/farclip 0</DIV>
<DIV>/farclip 25</DIV>
<DIV>/farclip 50</DIV>
<DIV>/farclip 100</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Great idea.&nbsp; It should allow any number between 0 and 100 of course.&nbsp; Then I can set up a hot key for my trader, and turn the clip down, set me AFK, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>By the way.&nbsp; Here's the syntax for your sig.&nbsp; &lt;a href="&nbsp;the URL to link, including http:// "&gt;My Junk&lt;/a&gt;&nbsp; Just paste the URL in between the quotes and you should be all set.&nbsp; I'm almost positive that you need the http:// in there too.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
